            <div class="project-info-wrapper mb-100">
                <div class="project-info-col">
                    <h4>About Netflix</h4>
                    <p>
                        Netflix is a simplified redesign of the popular streaming service. I have always loved Netflixs' approach to their design and wanted to attempt my own rendition of it. This was a fun, and interesting project which tested my Front-End skills with components such as a vertical navbar, mouse-hover tooltips and dynamic carousels. This is a NodeJS application, with Express routing, EJS templating, and SCSS styling.
                    </p>
                    <h4>In Retrospect...</h4>
                    <ul class="custom-list">
                        <li>Utilise a front end framework for better use of components</li>
                        <li>Use a third party library for the carousels</li>
                        <li>Populate the carousels with data through local JSON or back-end dabatase</li>
                        <li>Utilise a BEM approach for element naming</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="project-info-col">
                    <h4>Key Takeaways</h4>
                    <ul class="custom-list">
                        <li>More exposure to flexbox</li>
                        <li>Fixed, vertical navbar</li>
                        <li>Custom, vanilla JS carousels</li>
                        <li>Serving EJS Partials as dynamic components</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>Technology Used</h4>
                    <ul class="custom-list">
                        <li>NodeJS</li>
                        <li>SCSS</li>
                        <li>Express</li>
                        <li>EJS</li>
                        <li>Partials</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
